<font color="#FF0000">GRASS BY CARL SANDBURG</font><br>
<tt>Thu May 29 17:26:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
 &quot;Pile the bodies high at Austerlitz and Waterloo. Shovel them under and let me work- I am the grass; I cover all.  And pile them high at Gettysburg.  And pile them high at Verdun.  Shovel them under and let me work.  Two years, ten years, and passengers ask the conductor:  What place is this?  Where are we now?  I am the grass.  Let me work.&quot;  by Carl Sandburg, reprinted without permission by Nurse Ratchet, who hopes we *all* do everything we can, in any way we can, to ensure that no one forgets the sacrifices made by our fine servicemen and servicewomen.<br>

<p><code>--   (Nurse Ratchet) </code><p>


